"If you had asked me last year, all that mattered was to win a gold medal", he said.
"But you know, there are bigger things than Olympic gold medals.
My Olympic gold medal is Robbie".
Her son is named after his father Robert, who died in 2011 at age 40 after being diagnosed with brain cancer.
Daley said his father didn't accept the fact that he was going to die and one of the last things he asked was if they had tickets for the London 2012 games because he wanted to be in the front row.
"I couldn't tell him you're not gonna be around to be in the front row, Dad", he said.
"I was holding his hand when he stopped breathing and it was only when he really stopped breathing and died that I finally recognized that he was not invincible", she said.
The following year, Daley competed in the 2012 Olympics and earned a bronze medal.
"I was fully aware that this was what I had dreamed of all my life: diving in front of a crowd of my fellow citizens at the Olympic Games...there was no better feeling", he said.
